Source: English Language in Aust. & NZ, The
Author: TURNER
Vol / Page: 135
Edition:
Quote: In New Zealand the word Maori sometimes enters into slang..in a term like Maori P.T. (From the army PT = physical training) to mean lying down and doing nothing, what the Australian calls spinebashing.
